`WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` maps to Android's `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE`, which was deprecated in API 30 and no longer works reliably in .NET 10.

### Recommended fix: use MAUI's built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`

This is enabled by default in .NET MAUI and automatically scrolls content so the focused input stays visible. If you previously disabled it or it's not working, make sure:

**1. Don't override the soft input mode to `Resize`** — remove any old code like:

```csharp
// ❌ Remove this — deprecated and broken
App.Current.On<Android>()
   .UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust(WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize);
```

**2. If auto-scroll isn't kicking in**, explicitly enable it on your page or control:

```csharp
// In your page constructor or handler
#if ANDROID
KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect(AnimationStyle.FadeIn);
#endif
```

**3. If you need manual control** (e.g., a sticky bottom bar), handle window insets directly in your Android platform code:

```csharp
// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
using AndroidX.Core.View;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    // React to keyboard (IME) insets
    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new InsetsListener());
}

private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        // imeInsets.Bottom is the keyboard height in pixels
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
        return insets;
    }
}
```

### TL;DR

| Approach | When to use |
|---|---|
| `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (default) | Works for most input forms — just remove old `Resize` calls |
| `WindowInsetsCompat` listener | When you need pixel-precise control (chat input bars, sticky footers) |

For a chat screen with a sticky bottom input bar, the **insets listener** approach gives the best result — it moves your entire layout up by exactly the keyboard height.
